blog.title: Asks: OPEN! Submissions: OPEN!
blog.description:
(This is a roleplay blog run by @chickadee567)

((Talking out of character))

Hello there! I’m Professor Sakura, and I’m always willing

to help trainers and caretakers with their Pokemon.

You can ask me about Pokemon behavior, where certain Pokemon can be found,

and even report sightings of rare or mythical Pokemon.

((Search for the tag #rules to find rules for asks and submissions!))

question: How's Genesect doing?
answer:
They’re doing alright. I’ve been taking notes on their anatomy and behavior. I think they’ve become pretty attached to us….I might let them stay here.

- Professor Sakura

title: Pokemon of the Week - Nidoqueen
description:
Pokemon of the week - Noidoqueen

Ahh, back to the first generation!  Of the two Nidos, I’ve always had a softer spot for Nidoqueen.  Did you know that in the first generation, I’m pretty sure there were not enough Moonstones to evolve all 4 pokemon who evolved from them?  Tough choices had to be made!  Anyway, they start out so cute as little Nidos, and grow to be such impressive monsters!  Their forms are well through out and developed from the first through the third, they look like a natural evolution, which is just great.  I really like the coloring on Nidoqueen.  Sometimes the silhouette will make me think it’s a kangaskhan though!  But I really like the color scheme here too!

They have good solid stats, and a good move pool to use with them.  Their stats are not as good as they once were, due to power creep of the generations. (Can’t believe generation 8 is almost here!)  But they’ve still got what they need to make their presence known.

For using Nidoqueen is competitive play, please follow the link through to see what ideas they have.  They’re always good ones!
